scheduled the new trial for May in Los Angeles.
   Newton was in court Monday, flanked by his girlfriend, aides and
bodyguards.
   He sued NBC over three broadcasts in which NBC reported that
sources said Newton had gone to a reputed organized crime figure for
help with a problem. Newton testified at the 1986 trial that he was
seeking help in stopping death threats against his daughter.
